commit.message:
tidy up the top-level directory

m/ - man pages
p/ - packaging files
s/ - source code
t/ - tests

GNUmakefile: do not clobber $PATH

originally introduced to work around idiosyncracies
in my development environment, breaks the process
on *BSD systems.

update manpage, README

* fixed the SYNOPSIS
* manpage now has a FILES section for clarity
  and consistency with git-pimp

mailz.sendmail defaults to /usr/sbin/sendmail

IOW, full path.  /usr/sbin is where sendmail usually lives,
and this directory is not in non-root users' $PATH on ArchLinux,
openSUSE or SUSE machines for some reason.

make envelope sender more configurable

GIT_MAILZ_SENDER envvar and mailz.sender configuration.
identify internal errors in option handling

introduce usage function ala git-pimp...

... and document -h|--help.
test handling of bad options
handle options with getopts(1)
shuffle test cases around a little

tag error messages with "git-mailz: error: "

instead of "fatal: ".

dedup "fatal: " from error messages

`complain` updated from git-pimp.
use more descriptive testcase filenames
drop unused code (function o)
README, manpage: document the -f option properly

implement mailz.sendmail configuration

while GIT_MAILZ_SENDMAIL is sufficient, it's not comfortable
for regular use.
GNUmakefile: drop zshisms and obfuscating indirection
tests/a741380.patch -> tests/fixtures/

tests/tools.sh -> tests/setup

follow sibling project convention

GNUmakefile: 'check' runs in sanitized environment

* PATH needs attention
* zsh needs -f to skip most configuration files, while cram provides
  no support for command line options in --shell => welcome tests/tsh
GNUmakefile: first_in_path returns no leading ws
.gitignore += .bs-update

tests/dump-inputs elides body unless DUMP_INPUTS_FULL

no need to clutter tests with patch bodies

fix handling of directory arguments

`git-mailz dir` where `dir` had multiple files used
a concatenation of their pathnames as one.
tests excercise the directory argument path more
PKGBUILD: explicit checkdepends
PKGBUILD: make needs PREFIX=/usr

PKGBUILD: add missing checkdepends

i screwed this up in c199328c0cd0de82c8d2397d650d22b9b2cbf79f.

PKGBUILD, specfile: unbreak by dropping _upstreamver

support for non-tagged "releases" was gutted in
a9a113c32fc30640cc4bd0fbea3fa1815f9ea83f.

specfile: follow cram packaging changes

the package name is now just "cram", still in home:roman-neuhauser.
